title: Bug 110566Wrong data set result returned when set an invalid filter expression row[0]
description: When setting a filter expression like 'row[0] equals to 0', the data set result is incorrect. It either returns the wrong data set or returns a null result set.
OB: The data set result is incorrect when an invalid filter expression like 'row[0] equals to 0' is set.
EB: There should be a relevant error message that pops up.
SR:
To reproduce the issue:
1. Set a filter expression like 'row[0] equals to 0'.
2. Observe the data set result.
